ith in prayer and in need","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 29, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, taught us to bear witness to faith in prayer and to bear witness to faith in times of need. Bearing witness in prayer is to say, \u201cGreetings are for Allah, as are prayers and pure things.\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":8141,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/14\/preferred-tashahhud-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":2067,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Tashahhud: Variants of Prayer&#8217;s ending supplication","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 14, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would teach us the testimony of faith in prayer, just as he would teach us a chapter from the Quran. The Prophet would say, \u201cGreetings, blessings, prayers, and good words are for Allah. Peace be upon you,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33014,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/01\/what-to-say-final-tashahhud\/","url_meta":{"origin":2067,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Tashahhud: What to say at end of prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 1, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ka\u2019b ibn \u2018Urjah reported: We asked, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, how do we send blessings upon you and the people of the house? Allah has taught us how to send peace upon you.\u201d The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cSay: O Allah, send grace upon Muhammad and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4437,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/07\/end-salat-salaam-rahmah\/","url_meta":{"origin":2067,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Salat: The Prophet ends prayer with peace, mercy","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 7, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Wa\u2019il ibn Hujr reported: I prayed with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and he would end by invoking peace on his right side, saying, \u201cPeace be upon you, the mercy of Allah, and His blessings,\u201d and again to his left side, saying, \u201cPeace and mercy of Allah\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14615,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/06\/06\/dua-tashahhud-allah-prophet\/","url_meta":{"origin":2067,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Tashahhud: Supplication at the end of sitting in prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 6, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Fadalah ibn 'Ubayd reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, heard a man supplicating in his prayer, and he did not send blessing upon him. The Prophet said, \u201cThis man has rushed.\u201d Then, the Prophet called for the man or some others, and he said, \u201cWhen one of\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34843,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/12\/27\/hadith-khtubah-al-hajah\/","url_meta":{"origin":2067,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Khutbah al-Hajah: How the Prophet began his sermons","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 27, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, gave us the combination of all good things and their endings, for he taught us the statements of prayer and the statements of need. The statements of prayer are, \u201cAll greetings, prayers, and good things are\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2067","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=2067"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2067\/revisions"}],"wp:at